
[1]afflicted

   AFFLICT'ED, pp. Affected with continued or often repeated pain, either
   of body or mind; suffering grief or distress, of any kind; followed by
   at, by or with; as, afflicted at the loss of a child, by the
   rheumatism, or with losses.
